descript.abstract: There are no official zip code areas in Germany. Zip codes (Postleitzahl, PLZ) are related only to streets but are organized into the five-digit zip code areas that cover Germany. Germany Five-Digit Zip Code Areas (PLZgrenzen) represent these areas.
descript.purpose: Germany Five-Digit Zip Code Areas (PLZgrenzen) provides the five-digit zip code areas of Germany.
descript.supplinf: Largest scale when displaying the data: 1:100,000.

procstep.procdesc: There are no official zip code areas in Germany. Zip codes (Postleitzahl, PLZ) are only related to streets. To build the areas, ESRI Geoinformatik GmbH (ESRI Germany) digitized from topographic maps using community boundaries where possible, digitized from street lines inside cities and communities containing several zip codes, and used free interpretation.

The following steps were performed by ESRI: Extracted data set from ESRI PLZgrenzen 2000. Removed an attribute. Renamed attributes. Reduced an attribute's width. Added Region attribute. Created ArcGIS™ layer file (.lyr). Created ArcView legend file (.avl). Created projection file (.prj). Ran ArcView Avenue request ExportClean, and created spatial indices.

horizpa.horizpar: The positional accuracy of the coordinates does not exceed +/- 150 meters.

dataqual.logic: No duplicate features are present. The shapefile is exported using Avenue request ExportClean. This request verifies and enforces the correctness of shapes.
dataqual.complete: After processing, the data set is checked for drawing display and number of records and file sizes compared with source materials.
